Citation.sAbstract: Surface tensions at the temperatures of (283.15, 288.15, 293.15, 298.15, 303.15, 308.15, and 313.15) K  and isothermal (vapour + liquid) equilibrium at the temperatures of (288.15, 298.15, and 308.15) K of  n-hexane with 1-chlorobutane or 1-chloropentane mixtures have been measured. Surface tension measurements  were carried out with a drop volume tensiometer while the (vapour + liquid) equilibrium was  obtained using an all-glass dynamic recirculating type still. Several bulk thermodynamic properties of the  studied mixtures have been used together with the experimental measurements to analyse the results.  Furthermore, a thermodynamic study of surface formation, including interesting properties such as  excess surface compositions and excess properties of surface formation, is also presented.
Citation.sTitle: Surface and bulk behaviour of some (n-hexane + chloroalkane) mixtures
